cleaned_text: Dr. Kenzie Fuller is a Naturopathic Physician and Licensed Acupuncturist who is passionate about health of the whole family. She has special interest in fertility, pediatric and adolescent wellness, hormonal health, and diabetes management. She has additional training in IUD insertion, IUI procedure, and lactation education and supports all people in their journey to parenthood. Dr. Fuller graduated in 2021 from Bastyr University with a Doctorate in Naturopathic Medicine and a Masters in Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine. She integrates her training in conventional, naturopathic, and traditional Chinese medicine to find all-encompassing, sustainable, individualized plans for each patient. She is humbled to create collaborative relationships with her patients and assist them in finding optimal health and wellness. Growing up in Reno, NV, Dr. Fuller developed a love for the outdoors at a young age. When she is not seeing patients, she can be found hiking, biking, paddleboarding, baking cookies, and rooting on her alma mater, the Gonzaga bulldogs. Dr. Fuller is currently accepting all new patients.
